    <j.0:comment xml:lang="en">These draft Guidelines have been drafted in reply to the request of the Council and will be presented at the Industry and Telecommunications Council meeting of 4 April next, enabling thus the Council to reach its common position on the proposed Framework Directive. The draft Guidelines are based on existing jurisprudence and on the Commission's own decision-making practice in defining the relevant market and applying the concept of dominant position. The definitive version of the Guidelines will be adopted when the Framework Directive will be adopted. The current draft Guidelines, once approved by the Commission, will be discussed with the national regulatory and national competition authorities and, if necessary, be updated to take into account possible comments. For this reason, the text of the attached draft Guidelines is preliminary and does not necessarily reflect the Commission's final decision.</j.0:comment>
